description: Borrowed from French ptérygo-palatin, from New Latin pterygopalātīnus, from pterygoīdēs (“winglike”) +‎ palātīnus (“relating to the palate”); equivalent to pterygo- +‎ palatine.

entries.meaning: (anatomy, relational) Of or pertaining to the pterygoid process of the sphenoid bone and the palatine bone.
